        <h1> The Soul Of Tea </h1>
        <h2>by Aanya Sharma</h2>
        <hr>
        <p>
            In amber light the teapot gleams,
A keeper of our quiet dreams.
Each leaf unfurls, a whispered tale,
Of morning mists and mountain vale.
<br>
<br>
The world may rush, the hours flee,
Yet peace pours gently, cup to me.
No crown, no gold, no kingly key—
Can soothe the soul like humble tea.
<br>
<br>
It warms the heart, it clears the mind,
A friend both gentle, sweet, and kind.
Sip by sip, the day feels new—
Oh, simple tea, life’s purest brew.
<br>
<br>
        </p>
        <br>
